9
00:01:24,487 --> 00:01:25,761
告诉他吧 布赖恩
Tell him, Brian.

10
00:01:25,927 --> 00:01:29,522
昨晚我们和财政委员会紧急会面
We've had a meeting of the finance committee.

11
00:01:29,727 --> 00:01:32,605
阿斯顿浪子队得算总帐了
Aston Wanderers will have to call in the Receiver!

12
00:01:32,807 --> 00:01:36,243
你是说破产?     终场哨响了
You mean bankrupt? The final whistle.

13
00:01:36,447 --> 00:01:39,041
就缺150万磅 吉姆
We need one-and-a-half million quid, Jim.

14
00:01:39,207 --> 00:01:41,960
政府半分钟就浪费这么多
The government waste that every 30 seconds!

15
00:01:42,127 --> 00:01:45,517
这什么话      知道大家怎么说吗 吉姆?
Oh, I say! You know what people are saying?

16
00:01:45,727 --> 00:01:48,446
把地区议员捧成内阁大臣不合算
It's no good having a Cabinet Minister for an MP.

17
00:01:48,607 --> 00:01:51,405
还不如留他在地方上 照顾选区
Better a local lad with time for his constituency.

18
00:01:51,607 --> 00:01:53,086
胡扯     怎么?
That's absurd! Why?

19
00:01:53,247 --> 00:01:55,841
议员进了内阁 好处多得很
There are advantages if an MP's in the Cabinet.

20
00:01:56,007 --> 00:01:58,202
我们可没看到 是吧哈里
We haven't noticed them, have we, Harry

21
00:01:58,407 --> 00:02:01,922
比如?      比如反映选区的民愿
Such as? It reflects well on the constituency.

22
00:02:02,127 --> 00:02:04,322
结交有权有势的朋友
It's good to have powerful friends,

23
00:02:04,487 --> 00:02:07,399
从高层施加影响 解危救难...
Influence in high places, a friend in need...

24
00:02:07,567 --> 00:02:10,877
听着 朋友 现在需要150万磅救命钱
Listen, friend, what we need Is one-and-a-half million quid!

25
00:02:13,407 --> 00:02:15,716
你愿不愿意施加一下影响?
So will you use that influence to help us?

26
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:19,966
这个...我是说抽象的影响
Well, when I said influence, I meant the indefinable sort,

27
00:02:20,167 --> 00:02:24,365
无形的 潜在的优势
the intangible, subtle benefit

28
00:02:24,527 --> 00:02:28,236
在大政方针的初级阶段
of an input into broad general policy at its early stages

29
00:02:28,447 --> 00:02:31,166
朝有利选区的方向引导
while keeping constituency interests in mind.

30
00:02:32,167 --> 00:02:34,283
就是不行?
Do you mean no?

31
00:02:35,087 --> 00:02:36,839
这个...我大体愿意从根本上
Well, anything I can do in a broad,

32
00:02:37,007 --> 00:02:39,885
以它为目标 我当然会...
general sense to further the cause, I will certainly...

33
00:02:40,087 --> 00:02:41,486
出力
er, do.

34
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:45,597
如果我能的话 可是要一名大臣拨150万磅
If I can. But for a minister to pump one-and-a-half million

35
00:02:45,767 --> 00:02:47,485
支援他选区的足球队
into his local football club!

36
00:02:47,687 --> 00:02:49,245
他说不行
He means no.

37
00:02:49,447 --> 00:02:53,884
能拉选票啊 争取年轻人 你会成为选区的英雄
But there'd be lots of votes in it. You'd be the hero.

38
00:02:54,087 --> 00:02:58,285
"吉姆·哈克 阿斯顿队的救星" 终生保留议席
"The man who saved Aston Wanderers" Safe seat for life!

39
00:02:58,447 --> 00:03:02,201
媒体会大做文章 反对党也会 法官也会
That might occur to the press. And the opposition. And the judge!

40
00:03:02,407 --> 00:03:05,001
吉姆 这支队伍垮了 损失可惨重了
If this club goes to the wall It'll be a disaster.

41
00:03:05,167 --> 00:03:06,441
看看我们的战绩
Look at our history!

42
00:03:06,647 --> 00:03:10,196
英格兰足总杯 足联冠军 首次打入欧洲
FA Cup winners, League Champions, first team into Europe.

43
00:03:10,407 --> 00:03:12,284
我都知道 哈里 可是话说回来
I know all that, but be fair.

44
00:03:12,447 --> 00:03:15,280
这是地方事务 扯不上我们部
It's a local matter, not a ministerial one.

45
00:03:15,487 --> 00:03:18,445
布赖恩 你是文艺休闲委员会主席 你没办法吗?
As chair of the Arts and Leisure Committee, can you help?

46
00:03:18,647 --> 00:03:19,762
我? 别逗了
Me? You're joking.

47
00:03:19,927 --> 00:03:23,237
我花了半年争取711磅
I spent half of yesterday trying to raise 711 quid

48
00:03:23,447 --> 00:03:26,086
维修粮站美术馆的烟囱
to repoint the chimney on the art gallery.

49
00:03:26,287 --> 00:03:29,484
那家破美术馆? 让它垮了得了
That miserable place? Why not let it fall down?

50
00:03:29,687 --> 00:03:32,724
我倒没意见 不过万一砸到人 委员会要负责
I'd love to, but if it fell on somebody, the Council抯 liable.

51
00:03:32,887 --> 00:03:34,400
那破地方归我们管
We own the bloody place!

52
00:03:34,607 --> 00:03:37,246
不停有人出价要买
And we keep getting offers for the site.

53
00:03:37,407 --> 00:03:40,399
上个月一家旧货市场刚找过我们
Save fair Supermarkets were after it last month.

54
00:03:40,607 --> 00:03:43,246
等等 他们出多少?
Hold on, how much were they offering?

55
00:03:44,167 --> 00:03:46,556
好像是200万磅
About two million quid, I think.

56
00:03:46,767 --> 00:03:50,646
那你卖掉美术馆 球队就保住了
If you sold the art gallery, you could save the football club.

57
00:03:50,807 --> 00:03:54,356
规划署要质询的     能看看美术馆吗?
There'd have to be a planning enquiry. Can we see it?

58
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:57,365
赶快去 他们5点下班
We'll have to be quick. They close at five.

59
00:04:15,087 --> 00:04:18,602
还真破啊      2级保护建筑嘛
Hideous, isn't it? it抯 a Grade II listed building.

60
00:04:24,407 --> 00:04:27,638
伯纳 我们的政治领袖大人
Bernard, what is our political master up to

61
00:04:27,807 --> 00:04:30,446
对粮站美术馆打什么主意?
with the Corn Exchange Art Gallery

62
00:04:30,647 --> 00:04:35,675
哦 您怎么知道?     反正不是听你说的 伯纳
Oh, how did you find out about that? Not from you, Bernard.

63
00:04:35,887 --> 00:04:38,447
这个疏漏你要解释一下吗?
An omission you may care to explain.

64
00:04:39,687 --> 00:04:43,077
这当然只是选区事务吧?     当然不是
Surely it抯 just a constituency matter? Surely not.

65
00:04:43,287 --> 00:04:46,279
关闭美术馆 卖给旧货市场
Selling the gallery to Save fair Supermarkets

66
00:04:46,487 --> 00:04:49,718
价款无息贷给阿斯顿足球队
and giving an interest-free loan to Aston Wanderers,

67
00:04:49,887 --> 00:04:52,242
这是他作为议员而非大臣做的决定
he's acting as an MP not a minister.

68
00:04:52,447 --> 00:04:54,403
这是原则问题 伯纳
It is the principle, Bernard.

69
00:04:54,607 --> 00:04:57,997
你想不到后果会怎样吗?
Have you thought what the effect would be if this happens?

70
00:04:58,207 --> 00:05:00,482
他会急速窜红     正是
He'd be very popular. Exactly!

71
00:05:02,567 --> 00:05:05,718
红的发黑 红的可怕 然后呢?
Distressingly popular. Hideously popular. And then?

72
00:05:05,927 --> 00:05:11,797
大臣下届会连任      这不是我们的首要目标
The minister would be re-elected. And that is not our top priority.

73
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:16,606
对我们部来说 谁当大臣无足轻重
in this department, it makes little difference who the minister is.

74
00:05:16,807 --> 00:05:21,562
问题在于 要是别的球队也闹财政危机呢?
But the point is, suppose other football clubs got into difficulties?

75
00:05:21,767 --> 00:05:23,644
赛犬会呢?
And what about greyhound racing?

76
00:05:23,807 --> 00:05:27,322
补助了足球队 狗是不是也有份呢?
Should dog tracks be subsidised as well as football clubs?

77
00:05:27,527 --> 00:05:31,486
人们想要的话 怎么不行?     伯纳
Why not, if that's what the people want? Bernard...

78
00:05:32,327 --> 00:05:33,726
补助金...
subsidy...

79
00:05:34,767 --> 00:05:38,362
是给艺术 给文化的
Is for art, for culture.

80
00:05:40,007 --> 00:05:42,965
不是为了人们想要的东西
It is not to be given to what the people want!

81
00:05:44,807 --> 00:05:48,117
是为了人们不想要 又非得有的东西
It is for what the people don抰 want but ought to have!

82
00:05:49,367 --> 00:05:52,723
他们想要什么 自己会出钱的
If they want something they'll pay for it themselves!

83
00:05:52,927 --> 00:05:59,036
不 我们补助的是教化 修养 精神文明提升
No, we subsidise education, enlightenment, spiritual uplift.

84
00:05:59,247 --> 00:06:01,886
不是普通人的庸俗娱乐
Not the vulgar pastimes of ordinary people.

85
00:06:02,047 --> 00:06:05,676
如此歪风 万不可长 必须制止
It's the thin end of the wedge. It must be stopped!

86
00:06:06,407 --> 00:06:11,242
啊 大臣     汉弗莱 又怎么啦?
Ah, Minister. Humphrey. What's the matter now

87
00:06:11,447 --> 00:06:14,041
大臣 预先提醒您一下
Minister, I thought you'd like early warning

88
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:16,562
内阁近期要重组
that there's a reshuffle in the offing.

89
00:06:19,247 --> 00:06:23,525
该不是说...你不是...     不不 大臣
You don't mean... You're not suggesting... No, no, no, Minister.

90
00:06:23,727 --> 00:06:27,197
这回是部门权责再分配
There is to be a departmental reorganisation.

91
00:06:27,407 --> 00:06:29,637
是真的重组
A real reshuffle.

92
00:06:29,847 --> 00:06:32,725
我们可能会增加职责呢      有好处么?
We may get extra responsibilities. Do we want them?

93
00:06:32,927 --> 00:06:35,122
增加职责总是有好处的 大臣
We want all responsibilities, Minister,

94
00:06:35,287 --> 00:06:37,801
如果同时增加人手和预算的话
If they mean extra staff and bigger budgets.

95
00:06:38,007 --> 00:06:40,567
正是我们职责的广泛
It's the breadth of our responsibilities

96
00:06:40,727 --> 00:06:43,639
让我们有分量 让您有分量 大臣
that makes us important, makes you important.

97
00:06:43,847 --> 00:06:46,361
当您看到高楼大厦 人才济济
When you see vast buildings, huge staff

98
00:06:46,527 --> 00:06:49,280
巨额预算 您看出什么?
and massive budgets, what do you conclude?

99
00:06:49,927 --> 00:06:51,121
官僚主义?
Bureaucracy?

100
00:06:53,207 --> 00:06:57,086
不 大臣 应该看到在这一切顶峰
No, Minister, you conclude that at the summit

101
00:06:57,287 --> 00:07:00,404
高踞着一位伟大尊贵之人
there are men of great stature and dignity

102
00:07:00,567 --> 00:07:03,001
君临天下 指点江山
who hold the world in their hands

103
00:07:03,207 --> 00:07:05,482
所到之处莫不俯首称臣
and tread the earth like princes.

104
00:07:07,527 --> 00:07:09,006
对 我能看到
Yes, I see.

105
00:07:09,607 --> 00:07:12,838
所以新的职责要尽量攫取
So each new responsibility must be seized eagerly

106
00:07:13,047 --> 00:07:15,481
而旧的职责要严加保卫
and each old one guarded jealously.

107
00:07:15,687 --> 00:07:18,406
当然都是为您好 大臣
Entirely in your interests, of course, Minister.

108
00:07:18,567 --> 00:07:20,523
是哦 谢谢你提醒我 汉弗莱
Thank you for warning me, Humphrey.

109
00:07:20,727 --> 00:07:22,797
谢谢 大臣
Thank you, Minister.

110
00:07:24,127 --> 00:07:27,085
哦 对了...
Oh! By the way...

111
00:07:28,007 --> 00:07:31,363
关于粮站美术馆的提案
About the Corn Exchange Art Gallery proposal.

112
00:07:31,527 --> 00:07:32,596
怎么?
What about it?

113
00:07:32,807 --> 00:07:36,004
当然 那计划很有想象力 创意十足
It's the most imaginative scheme, novel idea,

114
00:07:36,207 --> 00:07:39,165
但我觉得是否不大明智?
but I wonder if it might not be a little unwise?

115
00:07:39,327 --> 00:07:40,316
为什么?
Why?

116
00:07:40,527 --> 00:07:43,405
一座贵重的居民福利设施      一座怪物
A valuable civic amenity. A monstrosity!

117
00:07:44,647 --> 00:07:47,115
一座贵重的居民福利怪物
A valuable civic monstrosity.

118
00:07:48,767 --> 00:07:50,997
可它藏有一批英国美术珍品
An important collection of British paintings.

119
00:07:51,167 --> 00:07:52,566
一点也不珍贵
Utterly unimportant.

120
00:07:52,767 --> 00:07:56,396
18世纪二流肖像 19世纪三流风景画
Second-rate portraits, third-rate landscapes,

121
00:07:56,607 --> 00:07:59,565
那些现代作品 泰特美术馆都不屑于收
modern paintings the Tate wouldn't even store.

122
00:07:59,767 --> 00:08:03,646
可这是对非珍品的珍贵收藏
an important collection of unimportant paintings.

123
00:08:03,847 --> 00:08:07,726
能大大提升过往居民的品味
And a source of great spiritual uplift to passing citizenry.

124
00:08:07,927 --> 00:08:10,919
他们从不进去      可他们知道它在那
They never go in! But they know it抯 there.

125
00:08:11,127 --> 00:08:14,676
馆长说平均每天只有11人参观
The curator says they average 11 visitors a day!

126
00:08:14,887 --> 00:08:19,005
再说这是选区事务 无关政府 你操什么心?
It's a constituency matter. What's your interest?

127
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:21,596
这是原则问题     原则?
A question of principle. Principle?

128
00:08:21,807 --> 00:08:24,765
您跟我说搞政治就是为了原则
What you used to tell me politics was about.

129
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:26,400
什么原则?
What principle?

130
00:08:26,567 --> 00:08:29,240
从原则上允许剥夺艺术经费
The principle of taking money away from the arts

131
00:08:29,447 --> 00:08:31,278
拿来支援足球这种东西
and putting it into football.

132
00:08:31,487 --> 00:08:33,921
足球俱乐部属于商业机构
A football club Is a commercial operation.

133
00:08:34,087 --> 00:08:37,204
就算它缺钱 也没理由发补贴
There's no cause for subsidy if it runs out of money.

134
00:08:37,407 --> 00:08:38,806
怎么没有?     怎么没有?
Why not? Why not?

135
00:08:39,007 --> 00:08:42,602
对啊 补贴艺术跟补贴足球都一样
Yes. There's no difference between subsidising football and art.

136
00:08:42,807 --> 00:08:45,605
除了群众更喜欢足球一些
Except more people are interested in football.

137
00:08:45,807 --> 00:08:48,367
我们的文化遗产必须保护
Our cultural heritage has to be preserved.

138
00:08:48,527 --> 00:08:49,596
为了谁?
For whom?

139
00:08:49,807 --> 00:08:54,085
为你们这些人 中产阶级知识分子
For people like you, you mean, the educated middle classes.

140
00:08:54,247 --> 00:08:58,035
凭什么大家贴钱让少数中产阶级享乐?
Why should others subsidise the pleasures of the middle-class few

141
00:08:58,247 --> 00:09:00,715
戏剧 歌剧 芭蕾
Theatre, opera, ballet!

142
00:09:00,927 --> 00:09:04,283
补贴艺术是中产阶级劫贫济富之举
Subsidising art Is a middle-class rip-off.

143
00:09:04,447 --> 00:09:07,245
大臣 您怎么能这么说?
Oh, Minister, how can you say such a thing?

144
00:09:07,447 --> 00:09:09,005
补贴的目的在于教育
Subsidy is about education,

145
00:09:09,167 --> 00:09:11,886
保护我们文明的精华
preserving the pinnacles of our civilisation.

146
00:09:12,087 --> 00:09:13,361
您没发现吗?
Or hadn抰 you noticed?

147
00:09:13,527 --> 00:09:16,121
不用你教我 汉弗莱 我也相信教育
Don't patronise me. I believe in education.

148
00:09:16,287 --> 00:09:20,678
提醒你 我是伦敦政经学院毕业的
I'm a graduate of the London School of Economics, remember.

149
00:09:20,887 --> 00:09:25,756
很高兴知道伦敦政经学院也不完全反对教育
Glad to learn even the LSE Is not opposed to education.

150
00:09:26,727 --> 00:09:30,083
补贴体育没什么不妥 体育也是教育
Nothing wrong with subsidising sport. Sport is educational.

151
00:09:30,287 --> 00:09:33,563
我们还有性教育 性也要补贴吗?
We have sex education too. Should we subsidise sex?

152
00:09:33,767 --> 00:09:35,086
可以吗?
Could we?

153
00:09:38,007 --> 00:09:42,478
让我们根据公众需要来发补贴
Let us choose what we subsidise by the extent of popular demand.

154
00:09:42,687 --> 00:09:46,646
这没有错 这是民主      可是大臣 这是导火索
It抯 democratic. it抯 the thin end of the wedge!

155
00:09:46,847 --> 00:09:49,315
长此以往 皇家歌剧院
What would happen to the Royal Opera House,

156
00:09:49,487 --> 00:09:52,047
我们文明的精粹会怎样呢?
the very summit of our cultural achievement?

157
00:09:52,247 --> 00:09:55,205
很好 就说皇家歌剧院 他们演什么?
Very good case in point. What do they do?

158
00:09:55,367 --> 00:09:57,597
莫扎特 瓦格纳 威尔第 普契尼
Mozart, Wagner, Verdi, Puccini.

159
00:09:57,767 --> 00:10:01,077
德国和意大利文化 没我们什么事
Germans and Italians, not our culture.

