Yes, I think that's all quite clear.

325
00:19:10,807 --> 00:19:13,685
为什么要我听这一团乱麻?
Why must I listen to this piddling gobbledegook?

326
00:19:15,407 --> 00:19:19,286
抱歉大臣 我认为这个机会能确保
I thought it would be an opportune moment for you to ensure

327
00:19:19,487 --> 00:19:21,842
在大臣您治理之下
that as a result of your ministerial efforts,

328
00:19:22,007 --> 00:19:24,919
地方理事会成员能得到更多会议津贴
local councillors will get more for attending meetings.

329
00:19:25,127 --> 00:19:28,005
哦 就是这个意思?     对
Oh, is that what it means? Yes.

330
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:31,239
好啊伯纳 你说得对 这是机会
Excellent. It is, as you say, opportune.

331
00:19:32,207 --> 00:19:35,995
我能不能再提个小建议?
And may I make one further small suggestion?

332
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:37,395
随便提
Be my guest.

333
00:19:37,847 --> 00:19:41,886
汉弗莱爵士昨晚会见了伊安惠沃爵士
Sir Humphrey had a word with Sir Ian Whitworth last night.

334
00:19:42,087 --> 00:19:45,284
伊安惠沃     美术馆是登记在案的建筑
Ian Whitworth! The Corn Exchange is a listed building,

335
00:19:45,487 --> 00:19:48,877
所以质询将由他手下一名调查员主持
so one of his planning inspectors will conduct the enquiry.

336
00:19:49,087 --> 00:19:53,046
汉弗莱爵士和伊安爵士会给他非正式指导方针
Sir Humphrey and Sir Ian will give him some informal guidelines.

337
00:19:53,207 --> 00:19:55,846
什么叫"非正式方针"?
How do you mean, "Informal guidelines"?

338
00:19:56,007 --> 00:20:00,319
指导方针没什么不对 人人都有工作方针
Everyone has guidelines for their work.

339
00:20:01,007 --> 00:20:04,044
规划调查员不是独立的吗?
I thought planning inspectors were impartial?

340
00:20:04,247 --> 00:20:06,078
真的 大臣
Oh, really, Minister!

341
00:20:06,287 --> 00:20:09,245
当然 火车也是独立的
So they are. Railway trains are impartial too.

342
00:20:09,447 --> 00:20:13,838
只要铺好轨道 它们照样跟着走
But if you lay down the lines for them, that's the way they go!

343
00:20:14,487 --> 00:20:17,638
可这不公平     这是政治 大臣
But that's not fair! it抯 politics, Minister.

344
00:20:17,847 --> 00:20:20,486
汉弗莱爵士怎么搞起政治来了?
What has Sir Humphrey got to do with politics?

345
00:20:20,647 --> 00:20:23,286
他是公务员 我负责政治
He's a civil servant. I'm the one in politics!

346
00:20:23,447 --> 00:20:25,483
对 大臣 确实是您负责
Yes, Minister, indeed you are!

347
00:20:26,807 --> 00:20:30,766
他们打算怎么对调查员施压?
How do they intend to put pressure on this planning inspector?

348
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:34,118
规划调查员有专门的等级制度
Planning inspectors have an independent hierarchy.

349
00:20:34,327 --> 00:20:37,399
只要知道谁想升职就行
A vulnerable one Is one anxious for promotion.

350
00:20:38,367 --> 00:20:41,723
怎么任命主持质询的调查员
How are planning inspectors chosen for an enquiry

351
00:20:41,887 --> 00:20:43,798
大臣能干涉吗?
Could a minister interfere?

352
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:47,642
大臣都是我们的主公     很好
Ministers are our lords and masters. Good.

353
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:51,045
环保部政务次官
The Paril Sec at the Department of the Environment

354
00:20:51,207 --> 00:20:53,084
是我的老朋友吉斯弗里曼
Is an old friend, Giles Freeman.

355
00:20:53,287 --> 00:20:56,006
如果弗里曼先生能安排一名
Well, if Mr Freeman could arrange for an inspector

356
00:20:56,167 --> 00:20:57,998
不在乎晋升的调查员
who didn抰 care about promotion,

357
00:20:58,207 --> 00:21:00,675
比如说 找个快退休的
lf, for instance, he's about to retire,

358
00:21:00,887 --> 00:21:03,082
他下结论时应该
he'll probably reach a verdict favouring

359
00:21:03,247 --> 00:21:05,556
更为公众而非部门着想
the community rather than the department.

360
00:21:06,247 --> 00:21:09,125
好 能帮我接吉斯的电话吗?
Good! Get me Giles on the phone, would you?

361
00:21:09,327 --> 00:21:11,283
他的私人秘书说他今晚
His Private Secretary says he can meet you

362
00:21:11,447 --> 00:21:13,961
投票之后在休息室等您
in the lobby after the vote this evening.

363
00:21:17,687 --> 00:21:20,997
伯纳 你想过从政吗?
Bernard, have you ever thought of gong into politics?

364
00:21:23,087 --> 00:21:25,237
我不想 大臣     为什么?
Oh, no, Minister. Why not?

365
00:21:25,447 --> 00:21:28,883
我在我的字典里定义过政治     怎么定义的?
I once looked it up in my thesaurus. What did it say?

366
00:21:29,087 --> 00:21:33,126
煽动 阴谋 操纵 推脱 贪赃枉法 蛊惑人心
Manipulation, intrigue, wire-pulling, evasion, graft, rabble-rousing...

367
00:21:33,327 --> 00:21:36,285
还是留给诸位主公来操心好了
I'd prefer to leave that to our lords and masters.

368
00:21:36,487 --> 00:21:39,047
我觉得我没有这些素质
I don't think I have the necessary qualities.

369
00:21:41,047 --> 00:21:44,198
可别低估你自己 伯纳
Don't underestimate yourself, Bernard!

370
00:21:44,407 --> 00:21:47,240
现在哈克拉拢到了吉斯弗里曼
Now it seems Hacker has got at Giles Freeman,

371
00:21:47,407 --> 00:21:49,363
我们部的政务次官
the Parli Sec in my department,

372
00:21:49,567 --> 00:21:53,765
他非要任命他的调查员 不要我那个
Appointing a different planning inspector to the one I chose

373
00:21:53,927 --> 00:21:56,885
他的调查员赞成哈克的计划
One who'd be sympathetic to Hacker's scheme.

374
00:21:57,087 --> 00:22:00,284
确实让人担心     担心? 这是死路一条
This is rather worrying. Worrying? it抯 desperate!

375
00:22:00,487 --> 00:22:03,320
很可能这个规划调查员
There's now every danger that the planning inspector

376
00:22:03,487 --> 00:22:05,364
会自己拿主意
could make up his own mind!

377
00:22:07,367 --> 00:22:10,757
当地人会热烈欢迎这个计划
There's likely to be huge local support for the scheme.

378
00:22:11,327 --> 00:22:12,919
我能帮什么忙?
But how can I help?

379
00:22:13,087 --> 00:22:16,079
我指望你出主意呢 阿诺德
I hoped you'd have some ideas, Arnold.

380
00:22:17,687 --> 00:22:20,645
等等 我想到了
Walt a minute! I've thought of something.

381
00:22:21,847 --> 00:22:25,965
下周部门重组的时候
When the departmental reorganisation occurs next week...

382
00:22:28,247 --> 00:22:32,604
你可以任命哈克为艺术总管大臣
you could make Hacker Cabinet Minister responsible for the arts!

383
00:22:33,447 --> 00:22:36,723
他不是化外之民吗?     对
But isn抰 he a complete philistine? Yes.

384
00:22:37,607 --> 00:22:41,566
反正工业部长也整天做无用功
But then the industry Secretary Is the idlest man in town.

385
00:22:46,207 --> 00:22:48,767
教育部长没教养
The Education Secretary is illiterate!

386
00:22:51,247 --> 00:22:54,125
就业部长该失业
The Employment Secretary Is unemployable!

387
00:22:55,127 --> 00:22:58,085
这倒是 好主意 汉弗莱
Quite. That's good thinking, Humphrey.

388
00:22:58,287 --> 00:23:02,041
哈克当了艺术总管大臣
Hacker can hardly start out as Cabinet Minister for the arts

389
00:23:02,207 --> 00:23:04,243
不能首先就拆美术馆
by closing down an art gallery.

390
00:23:04,447 --> 00:23:07,166
正是     但这不是内阁改组吧?
Exactly. But it抯 not a reshuffle, is it?

391
00:23:07,327 --> 00:23:09,477
不 只是职能重新分配
No, I simply meant reorganise.

392
00:23:09,647 --> 00:23:12,286
将艺术和广播电视
Move the arts and telecommunications

393
00:23:12,487 --> 00:23:15,479
划入行政部管辖范围
into the purview of the DAA.

394
00:23:15,647 --> 00:23:18,445
艺术和电视?
Arts and television together?

395
00:23:18,607 --> 00:23:21,121
它俩有什么联系?
What have they got to do with each other?

396
00:23:22,287 --> 00:23:24,517
死对头嘛
They're complete opposites.

397
00:23:24,727 --> 00:23:27,400
不会造成一个霸王部门吧?
Wouldn抰 we be creating a monster department?

398
00:23:27,567 --> 00:23:30,240
你们已经掌握地方政府了
You've already got local government as well.

399
00:23:30,407 --> 00:23:33,240
艺术和地方政府天生一对
Arts and local government go well together.

400
00:23:33,407 --> 00:23:34,442
怎么讲?
How so?

401
00:23:35,367 --> 00:23:38,086
老乡骗老乡也是一门艺术
Well, the art of jiggery-pokery!

402
00:23:40,327 --> 00:23:43,683
你确实是刚刚想到的吧?
You only just thought of this here and now, did you?

403
00:23:44,927 --> 00:23:49,364
是啊 怎么?     你也是艺术家 对吗?
Yes, why? Bit of an artist yourself, aren't you?

404
00:23:50,087 --> 00:23:51,839
哦 阿诺德
Oh, Arnold!

405
00:23:53,607 --> 00:23:57,236
还有事吗 伯纳?     大臣 您会见足球队之前
Anything more, Bernard? Sir Humphrey wants a word

406
00:23:57,407 --> 00:24:00,126
汉弗莱爵士有话要说
before your meeting about Aston Wanderers.

407
00:24:00,327 --> 00:24:02,682
他不知道我不会动摇吗?
But I'm unshakeable on that!

408
00:24:02,887 --> 00:24:05,117
没用的 汉弗莱 我决心已定
It's no good, Humphrey, my mind is made up.

409
00:24:05,327 --> 00:24:09,366
尽管如此 大臣 内阁改组有新消息了
You might be interested in a new development

410
00:24:09,527 --> 00:24:13,998
你说只是再分配的     不只是再分配
You said it was just a reorganisation. Not just a reorganisation.

411
00:24:14,407 --> 00:24:16,238
而是再分配
A reorganisation.

412
00:24:18,127 --> 00:24:20,960
我荣幸地宣布 它给我们部
I'm delighted to tell you that it has brought us,

413
00:24:21,127 --> 00:24:23,402
给您增加了荣耀和分量
brought you, new honour and importance.

414
00:24:23,607 --> 00:24:26,565
在现有的职责之上
In addition to existing responsibilities,

415
00:24:26,727 --> 00:24:30,640
您又被任命为艺术总管大臣
you will be Cabinet Minister responsible for the arts.

416
00:24:36,487 --> 00:24:38,682
是吗 这是好事啊
I say, that's rathergood, isn抰 it!

417
00:24:38,847 --> 00:24:41,122
等等 你怎么比我还先知道?
Hold on, how do you know before I do?

418
00:24:41,327 --> 00:24:43,887
内阁秘书作出决定之后
I just happened to be with the Cabinet Secretary

419
00:24:44,047 --> 00:24:46,277
我刚好在他身边
shortly after the decision was taken.

420
00:24:46,487 --> 00:24:47,886
这样啊
I see.

421
00:24:48,047 --> 00:24:51,005
艺术总管大臣
Cabinet Minister with responsibility for the arts!

422
00:24:51,207 --> 00:24:53,641
这样啊      可不是吗
Well, well, well! Yes, indeed.

423
00:24:53,847 --> 00:24:56,486
好啊汉弗莱 还有事吗? 我有会要开
Anything more? I'm about to start a meeting.

424
00:24:56,687 --> 00:24:58,166
对了 那个会
Oh, the meeting, yes.

425
00:24:58,327 --> 00:25:01,160
大臣 我衷心希望您站在新角度
I do hope you've considered the implications

426
00:25:01,327 --> 00:25:03,887
考虑此事的影响
of your new appointment on the subject.

427
00:25:04,367 --> 00:25:07,165
拯救一支足球队?     不不
Rescuing a football club? No, no.

428
00:25:07,367 --> 00:25:09,278
不知道别人会怎么看
I was wondering how it would look

429
00:25:09,447 --> 00:25:11,802
您作为艺术总管大臣
If as Minister responsible for the arts,

430
00:25:12,007 --> 00:25:14,646
上任头一件事就拆美术馆
your first act was to knock down an art gallery.

431
00:25:30,767 --> 00:25:33,076
那美术馆其实不错的...
It's quite a decent little art gallery...

432
00:25:35,047 --> 00:25:36,844
就是     建筑挺有意思
Exactly. Interesting building.

433
00:25:37,047 --> 00:25:40,005
2级保护建筑     大臣 您该开会了
Grade II listed. Minister, your meeting...

434
00:25:41,607 --> 00:25:44,724
天啊 我该怎么说?
Oh, my God! What am I gong to say?

435
00:25:45,927 --> 00:25:50,205
威金森 诺博和格林议员      布赖恩 幸会
Councillors Wilkinson, Noble and Green. Brian, good to see you.

436
00:25:50,407 --> 00:25:52,682
彼得 道格
Pete... Doug.

437
00:25:52,887 --> 00:25:55,845
这是汉弗莱阿普比爵士 我的常任秘书
Sir Humphrey Appleby, my Permanent Secretary.

438
00:25:56,047 --> 00:25:58,686
那他是临时秘书?
You mean he's only a temp!

439
00:26:01,367 --> 00:26:04,564
形势一片大好 我们争取到了所有政党
It's gong great. We've got all the political parties with us

440
00:26:04,727 --> 00:26:06,240
郡议会也支持
and the County Council.

441
00:26:06,447 --> 00:26:08,756
只等你们部批准
All we need is your approval for using

442
00:26:08,927 --> 00:26:12,078
把款项贷给足球队就行了
the sale of the art gallery as a loan to the club.

443
00:26:13,887 --> 00:26:16,879
这个 恐怕有点问题
Well, I'm afraid there's a snag.

444
00:26:17,047 --> 00:26:19,481
你说没问题的     呃 现在有了
You said there weren't any! Well, there is.

445
00:26:20,967 --> 00:26:23,401
怎么?      问题在于...这个...
Well, it抯 just that... Well...

446
00:26:23,607 --> 00:26:25,916
似乎...貌似...
It appears... Well, it seems...

447
00:26:27,167 --> 00:26:29,965
应该说问题出现于...
Well, I should say it has emerged...

448
00:26:31,527 --> 00:26:34,246
我想汉弗莱爵士比我清楚
Sir Humphrey can explain better than me.

449
00:26:38,567 --> 00:26:44,085
做不到 先生们 那家美术馆是...合伙基金
It can't be done, gentlemen. Er, the art gallery is... it抯 a trust.

450
00:26:44,247 --> 00:26:47,956
规定专款专用的      对 是合伙基金
Terms of the original bequest. Yes, it抯 a trust.

451
00:26:48,167 --> 00:26:51,045
我们得拆别的建筑
We shall have to knock something else down!

452
00:26:51,207 --> 00:26:55,405
学校 教堂 医院 肯定能腾出地来
School, church, hospital... There's bound to be something!

453
00:26:55,567 --> 00:26:59,082
真不敢相信 你要我回去告诉大家
I can't believe this. So I have to tell people back home

454
00:26:59,247 --> 00:27:01,238
说你出尔反尔?
you've gone back on your word?

455
00:27:01,447 --> 00:27:04,245
是你自己的主意啊     不是我 是法律不允许
It was your own idea! it抯 not me, it抯 the law.

456
00:27:04,447 --> 00:27:07,245
你早干吗去了 现在才发现?
Why didn抰 you find out till now

457
00:27:08,407 --> 00:27:10,204
这个...
Well...

458
00:27:20,047 --> 00:27:23,005
那我挑明了告诉你
Let me be absolutely frank with you.

459
00:27:23,527 --> 00:27:29,079
实际上 这事有可能 仅仅是可能成功
It would be possible to push this through

460
00:27:29,287 --> 00:27:33,246
不过要拖很久     拖呗 已经这么久了
but it would take an awful long time. Ok, we've spent enough.

461
00:27:33,407 --> 00:27:37,798
问题在于 这就要放弃另一件事
Trouble is, something else would have to go by the board.

462
00:27:38,007 --> 00:27:40,475
我手头正忙着的事
The thing that's taking my time at the moment

463
00:27:40,647 --> 00:27:43,445
是要争取增加地方议员经费
Is forcing through councillors' expenses

464
00:27:43,607 --> 00:27:46,167
和会议津贴
and attendance allowances.

465
00:27:47,167 --> 00:27:50,876
我不能同时对两边施压
I can't put my personal weight behind both schemes.

466
00:27:53,047 --> 00:27:57,962
那就放弃地方议员涨津贴的事
Forget about the increased allowances for councillors

467
00:27:58,167 --> 00:28:02,285
专心解决卖美术馆的法律问题
and concentrate on the legal obstacles, the sale of the art gallery.

468
00:28:02,447 --> 00:28:07,965
法律问题很难搞的      这回尤其难搞
Tricky things, legal obstacles. This is a particularly tricky one.

469
00:28:08,127 --> 00:28:10,687
就算费尽心思 最后还可能功亏一篑
At the end of the day, you might still fall.

470
00:28:12,487 --> 00:28:16,196
都没准的     如果这样的话...
Every possibility. If that's the way it is...

471
00:28:16,407 --> 00:28:18,841
我们有可能计划
there's a chance we might want to close

472
00:28:19,007 --> 00:28:21,680
年末关闭爱丁山小学
Edgehill primary at the end of the year...

473
00:28:21,887 --> 00:28:25,243
那块地也能卖个一两百万
That site would fetch a couple of million, give or take.

474
00:28:25,447 --> 00:28:29,201
好吧 就这么办 不会跟你过不去
Well, there it is, then. No ill feelings to you.

475
00:28:29,407 --> 00:28:31,238
好的 那你回地方上解释
Good. And you'll explain locally

476
00:28:31,407 --> 00:28:33,967
我们绕不过法律规定?
that we can't overcome the legal obstacles?

477
00:28:34,167 --> 00:28:37,477
尽管放心 继续努力吧
'Course we will. Carry on with the good work!

478
00:28:42,967 --> 00:28:46,516
大臣 您真是艺术家
Oh, Minister, a work of art.

479
00:28:49,447 --> 00:28:54,202
恕我失陪 我要去换衣服了    又是工作聚会?
If you'll excuse me, I have to dress. Another works' outing?

480
00:28:58,007 --> 00:29:00,646
呃 汉弗莱     大臣?
Er, Humphrey... Minister?

481
00:29:00,807 --> 00:29:04,846
作为艺术总管大臣
As Cabinet Minister responsible for the arts...

482
00:29:07,767 --> 00:29:09,200
我能一起去吗?
could I come too?

483
00:29:11,127 --> 00:29:12,606
是 大臣
Yes, Minister!

